	article#daizsa-jackson
		header.bhm-article-header(aria-level="3")
			h1.bhm-mobile(aria-hidden="true") Daizsa Jackson 
			img(src="/01-Intro-Collage.jpg" alt="")
			.bhm-article-header-content
				h1.bhm-mobile-hidden Daizsa Jackson 
				p Social Media Specialist, Daizsa Jackson manages Dr. Martens social influencer program. Self-proclaimed bookworm and textbook bibliophile, Daizsa is passionate about Black literature. No matter the genre, you can count on her recommendations. Daizsa kindly shared her reading list which features some of her favorite Black writers. 
		
		+vimeoVideo("681098837", "Daizsa Jackson", "/daizsa-film-overlay.jpg")

		section.bhm-photo(data-src="/02-Zora.jpg" aria-description="Archival image of Zora Neale Houston wearing a hat and wood bead necklace looking down and off to the side.")
			img.bhm-photo-image
			.bhm-photo-cover
				h2 Zora Neale Hurston
				p Was a #[a(href="https://www.zoranealehurston.com/" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) world-renowned author], anthropologist, and filmmaker during the Harlem Renaissance of the 1920s in New York City. She wrote four novels and over fifty short stories, plays, and essays over the course of her life. She is an inspiration for many writers and readers. 
		
		section.bhm-looping-video
			video(loop autoplay muted playsinline)
				source(src="/harlem-web.mp4" type="video/mp4")
			.bhm-looping-video-text
				h2 Harlem Renaissance 
				p A #[a(href="https://www.history.com/topics/roaring-twenties/harlem-renaissance" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) cultural revival] of new ideas and Black artistic expression during the 1920s centered in the Harlem neighborhood of New York City. It was an explosion of talent! This era is responsible for some of the greatest American artists of all time; Louis Armstrong, Zora Neale Hurston, and Langston Hughes to name a few.
			
		section.bhm-photo(data-src="/03-Kiese.jpg" aria-description="Archival image of Zora Neale Houston wearing a hat and wood bead necklace looking down and off to the side.")
			img.bhm-photo-image
			.bhm-photo-cover
				h2 Kiese Laymon 
				p #[a(href="https://www.kieselaymon.com/" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) Kiese] is a Black southern writer whose work has garnered multiple awards and accolades. His book Heavy: An American Memoir was named one of the 50 Best Memoirs of the Past 50 Years by The New York Times. He has several new projects in the works including a reading and writing program for kids and their parents. 
		
		section.bhm-quote
			.bhm-quote-body So much content has been centered around our struggles, but over time Black authors have ventured outside of that box and have told more honest stories. The good and the bad and everything in between.
			.bhm-quote-citation Daizsa Jackson
		
		section.bhm-reading-list(style="background-image:url(/04-reading-list.jpg);")
			h2 Daizsa's Recommended Reading List:
			h3 Find your next favorite author.
			ul
				li #[strong Homegoing] by #[a(href="https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/authors/2117741/yaa-gyasi/" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) Yaa Gyasi]
				li #[strong Heavy: An American Memoir] by #[a(href="https://www.kieselaymon.com/heavy" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) Kiese Laymon]
				li #[strong The Secret Lives of Church Ladies] by #[a(href="https://www.deeshaphilyaw.com" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) Deesha Philyaw]
				li #[strong The Vanishing Half] by #[a(href="https://britbennett.com" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) Brit Bennett]
				li #[strong Open Water] by #[a(href="https://www.instagram.com/caleb_anelson/?hl=en" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) Caleb Azumah Nelson]
				li #[strong Everything Inside] by #[a(href="https://edwidgedanticat.com" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) Edwidge Danticat]
				li #[strong Love in Color] by #[a(href="https://www.bolubabalola.com" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) Bolu Babalola]
				li #[strong Caul Baby] by #[a(href="http://www.morgan-jerkins.com" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) Morgan Jerkins]
				li #[strong Children of Blood and Bone] by #[a(href="https://www.tomiadeyemi.com" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) Tomi Adeyemi]
				li #[strong When No One is Watching: A Thriller] by #[a(href="https://alyssacole.com/" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) Alyssa Cole]

		footer.bhm-footer
			img(src="/fbwl-charity.png" style="width:180px;margin-bottom:30px;")
			p Upon Daizsa's recommendation, Dr. Martens is donating $5,000 to The Free Black Women's Library. &#x22;There's a lack of community and spaces dedicated to uplifting and celebrating Black female writers specifically. I love that this organization is committed to creating those spaces.&#x22; &#x2014; Daizsa Jackson 
			a.bhm-external(href="https://www.thefreeblackwomenslibrary.com/" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) Learn More


